Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Frontend Software Engineer* position with *Andiamo Talent Partners*. I bring over three years of professional experience building responsive web applications with React and TypeScript, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade frontend systems that directly reflect *the technical depth and user-focused design this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I built responsive and accessible web applications using React and TypeScript that translate natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous frontend-backend API integration, state management, and intuitive UI component design. I developed generative code solutions including React component templates and API-aware SDK patterns to accelerate frontend and backend API integration with platform services, improving implementation correctness and developer experience. To ensure production quality, I enabled robust observability using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to monitor user experience, debug failures, and track quality over time. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with responsive layouts and accessible UI components. I integrated frontend interfaces with backend APIs using React and TypeScript, implementing state management patterns and HTML/CSS best practices to ensure seamless user experience across the platform. I participated in code reviews and shipped features through CI/CD pipelines, collaborating with product and design teams on user experience improvements — directly mirroring *the collaborative, quality-driven engineering culture this role demands*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *build elegant web interfaces and contribute meaningfully to the team's core frontend engineering responsibilities*.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical communication and collaborative problem-solving — skills that translate directly into *the attention to detail and strong communication skills this team values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion to generate industry-standard fashion designs, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, demonstrating strong communication skills and attention to detail. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with precision and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *Andiamo's mission of building high-impact teams and supporting the AI revolution*.

I have always been passionate about *building high-impact teams and supporting the AI revolution through innovative technology solutions*, and I am excited about Andiamo's mission to *deliver measurable human capital growth and elevate the recruiting industry*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

